Normal Distribution Calculations

Binomial Experiment

  1. Fixed number of independent and identical trials
  • 10 tosses of coinst
  • check 20 randomly selected people for blood type
  1. Outcome of each trial falls into 1 of 2 categories - success or failure
  2. Probability remains the same from trial to trial

If you sampling without replacement and sample size is very small it is not a binomial experiment.

cum.round20 <- NULL
cum.reps <- 1000

{

  #net.winnings
  cum.winnings <- cumsum(net.winnings)
  cum.round20[i] <- cum.winnings[20]
